The paper proposes a method for extracting hierarchical relationships from bipartite networks, which is a topic related to social network analysis and data mining. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also involves statistical modeling and machine learning techniques, which are relevant to cs.SD (Software Engineering), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the proposed method to ontology extraction, which is a topic related to information retrieval and natural language processing, hence cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
